Solution:
The roots of $z^{1997} - 1 = 0$ are the 1997th roots of unity, which lie on the circle $|z| = 1$ centered at the origin.  Let $v = \operatorname{cis} \theta$ and $w = \operatorname{cis} \phi,$ where $0 \le \theta, \phi < 2 \pi$ and $\theta \neq \phi.$  Then
\[v + w = (\cos \theta + \cos \phi) + i (\sin \theta + \sin \phi).\]By the Law of Cosines,
\[\cos (\theta - \phi) = \cos \theta \cos \phi + \sin \theta \sin \phi = \frac{v \overline{w} + \overline{v} w}{2}.\]Then
\begin{align*}
|v + w|^2 &= (\cos \theta + \cos \phi)^2 + (\sin \theta + \sin \phi)^2 \\
&= 2 + 2 \cos \theta \cos \phi + 2 \sin \theta \sin \phi \\
&= 2 + 2 \cos (\theta - \phi).
\end{align*}Hence, $\sqrt{2 + \sqrt{3}} \le |v + w|$ if and only if $\cos (\theta - \phi) \ge \frac{\sqrt{3}}{2}.$

