Let $H$ be the orthocenter of triangle $ABC.$  Then $AH,$ $BH,$ and $CH$ are perpendicular to $BC,$ $AC,$ and $AB,$ respectively.

[asy]
import three;

size(180);
currentprojection = perspective(6,3,2);

triple A, B, C, H;

A = (1,2,3);
B = (5,3,1);
C = (3,4,5);
H = foot(A,B,C);

draw(B--C--A--B);
draw(H--A);
draw(H--B);
draw(H--C);

label("$A$", A, N);
label("$B$", B, S);
label("$C$", C, E);
label("$H$", H, S);
[/asy]

Let $\mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 2 \\ 3 \end{pmatrix},$ $\mathbf{b} = \begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ 3 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix},$ and $\mathbf{c} = \begin{pmatrix} 3 \\ 4 \\ 5 \end{pmatrix}.$  Then vectors $\overrightarrow{BC} = \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{b} = \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 1 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix}$ and $\overrightarrow{AB} = \mathbf{b} - \mathbf{a} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 1 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix},$ so the normal vector to plane $ABC$ is
\[\mathbf{n} = \overrightarrow{BC} \times \overrightarrow{AB} = \begin{pmatrix} 18 \\ 14 \\ 6 \end{pmatrix}.\]Hence, the equation of plane $ABC$ is $18x + 14y + 6z = 70.$

Let $H = (h_1,h_2,h_3).$  Then $AH$ is perpendicular to plane $BC,$ so the vector $\begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 1 \\ h_2 - 2 \\ h_3 - 3 \end{pmatrix}$ is parallel to $\mathbf{n}.$  Hence,
\[\begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 1 \\ h_2 - 2 \\ h_3 - 3 \end{pmatrix} = k \mathbf{n} = \begin{pmatrix} 6k \\ 7k \\ 3k \end{pmatrix}\]for some scalar $k.$  Since $AH$ is also perpendicular to $BC,$ $BH$ is perpendicular to $AC,$ and $CH$ is perpendicular to $AB,$ we must have
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{a} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 1 \\ h_2 - 2 \\ h_3 - 3 \end{pmatrix} &= \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{a} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 1 \\ h_2 - 2 \\ h_3 - 3 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 4 \\ 1 \\ -2 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 6k \\ 7k \\ 3k \end{pmatrix}, \\
\mathbf{a} - \mathbf{b} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 5 \\ h_2 - 3 \\ h_3 - 1 \end{pmatrix} &= \mathbf{c} - \mathbf{b} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 5 \\ h_2 - 3 \\ h_3 - 1 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} -2 \\ 1 \\ 4 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 6k \\ 7k \\ 3k \end{pmatrix}, \\
\mathbf{b} - \mathbf{c} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 3 \\ h_2 - 4 \\ h_3 - 5 \end{pmatrix} &= \mathbf{a} - \mathbf{c} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} h_1 - 3 \\ h_2 - 4 \\ h_3 - 5 \end{pmatrix} = \begin{pmatrix} 5 \\ 3 \\ 1 \end{pmatrix} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} 6k \\ 7k \\ 3k \end{pmatrix}.
