B = (3,0);
C = 1.5*dir(60);
D = (A + B)/2 + sqrt(2)/2*(C - (A + B)/2);

draw(A--B--C--cycle);
draw(D--(D + 2*dir(30)),dashed);
draw(D--(D + 2*dir(-90)),dashed);
draw(D--(D + 2*dir(150)),dashed);

label("$A$", A, SW);
label("$B$", B, SE);
label("$C$", C, N);
label("$O'$", D, S);
[/asy]

Hence,
\[\frac{\sqrt{3}}{2} \cdot \frac{s}{\sqrt{2}} = 1,\]so $s = \boxed{\frac{2 \sqrt{6}}{3}}.$
